    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Ok for future reference, helper.state.addDisjunctiveFacet creates a new state that's why it's not working. To make it work, one should:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nhelper.setState(helper.state.addDisjunctiveFacet);\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen adding the disjunctive facet you don't need to do a `search()` in the init, a subsequent search will be done anyway.",
    "created_at": "2017-04-18T17:15:42Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2004#issuecomment-294915298",
